4 involves GFR less than 15","Stage 5 involves GFR between 15-29"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe classification of CKD by GFR is:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage 1\u003C/strong\u003E: GFR \u0026gt; 90 with evidence of kidney damage\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage 2\u003C/strong\u003E: GFR 60-89\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage 3a\u003C/strong\u003E: GFR 45-59\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EStage 3b: GFR 30-44\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage 4\u003C/strong\u003E: GFR 15-29\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage 5\u003C/strong\u003E: GFR \u0026lt; 15\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEvidence of kidney damage in Stage 1 may include albuminuria, haematuria, or structural abnormalities on imaging. Stage 5 is also known as kidney failure or end-stage kidney disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Chronic kidney disease is classified into 5 stages based on glomerular filtration rate (GFR)","Stage 3 CKD is subdivided into 3a (GFR 45-59) and 3b (GFR 30-44)","Stage 5 CKD (kidney failure) is defined as GFR less than 15 mL/min/1.73m\u00b2"],"references":["Chen TK, Knicely DH, Grams ME. Chronic Kidney Disease Diagnosis and Management: A Review. JAMA. 2019 Oct 1;322(13):1294-1304. doi: 10.1001/jama.2019.14745. PMID: 31573641; PMCID: PMC7015670","Vaidya SR, Aeddula NR. Chronic Kidney Disease. [Updated 2024 Jul 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK535404/","Jennette, J. C., \u0026 D\u0027Agati, V. D. (2023). Heptinstall\u0027s Pathology of the Kidney. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Koeppen, B. M., \u0026 Stanton, B. A. (2018). Renal Physiology E-Book: Renal Phy